The paper deals with coordinated beamforming in a multiple-input single-output interference channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problem formulation and constraints on individual probability of rate outage and power budget suggest that the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of weighted sum rate and max-min-fairness rate as system utilities indicates that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
